>[Question]
>In 1994 al unser, jr., reached a speed of 160.872 miles per hour in 
>the Indianapolis 500 automobile race.  Write an equivalent decimal 
>for this number.
>
>[Difficulty]
>the number of zeros that need to be put behind the number
>
>[Thoughts]
>160.8720

It doesn't matter how many zeros you add; you've made an equivalent
decimal, and you can make others by adding more zeros. It's up to you.

